{"pageProps":{"tutorial":{"title":"MySQL Database Creation","slug":"mysql-create-database","subject":"MySQL","category":"Database","level":"Beginner","estimated_read_time":"10 mins","prerequisites":["MySQL Installation & Setup","MySQL Data Types"],"learning_objectives":["Create a new Database","Show available databases","Select a database for use","Drop a database"],"theory":"## Managing Databases\nBefore you create tables, you must create a container for them, which is the **Database** (or Schema).\n\n### Creating a Database\nThe `CREATE DATABASE` statement is used to create a new SQL database.\n\n### Seeing Databases\nTo see which databases exist on the server, use `SHOW DATABASES;`.\n\n### Selecting a Database\nBefore running queries on tables, you must tell MySQL which database you are working with using the `USE` statement.\n\n### Dropping a Database\nTo delete a database (and all its tables/data forever), use `DROP DATABASE`.","syntax":"CREATE DATABASE [IF NOT EXISTS] database_name;\nUSE database_name;\nDROP DATABASE [IF EXISTS] database_name;","examples":[{"code":"CREATE DATABASE school;\nSHOW DATABASES;\nUSE school;","output":"Database changed","explanation":"Creates a DB named 'school', lists it, and then selects it as the active database."}],"common_mistakes":[{"mistake":"Forgetting to select the database.","correction":"If you don't run `USE db_name`, extracting tables will fail with 'No database selected'.","example":"CREATE TABLE students... -> Error 1046."},{"mistake":"Dropping the wrong database.","correction":"`DROP DATABASE` is irreversible. Always double-check.","example":"DROP DATABASE production; (Catastrophic)"}],"interview_questions":[{"question":"What is the difference between Schema and Database in MySQL?","answer":"In MySQL, Schema and Database are synonymous. `CREATE SCHEMA` is an alias for `CREATE DATABASE`.","difficulty":"Easy"}],"practice_problems":[{"problem":"Create a database named 'inventory'. Check if it exists. Delete it.","hint":"